08F28EFD.Line13.53D3D: A bairn was born healthy a fortnight ago, praise the Glór-an-Fháidha, but the mother is weak. Darcel stole the runic charm I placed to heal her.

0E45AD9B.Line20.53D3D: Bastard probably just wanted quick coin. He may have condemned both mother and child. Deal with him and bring the charm back.

99BCBDAD.Line1.53D3D.Bar: Aye! A thief named Darcel snuck in with the knights posing as muscle. Took something of mine.

99BCC863.Line1.53D3D.Dru: Indeed, master Druid. A thief named Darcel snuck in with the knights posing as muscle. Best we handle the matter ourselves, rather than ask the knights for aid.
